Twitter reactions highlight praise for Jr NTR and Khan's performances, with some reviewers noting the film's occasional grounding in reality. The film's U.S. pre-sales surpassed those of "Salaar."

name: Oakland Athletics
summary: The Oakland Athletics (A's) are leaving Oakland after 57 years, leaving fans heartbroken and facing a sense of loss ("Oakland baseball fans coming to grips with Athletics’ departure"). Some fans express relief at the team's departure, blaming the team's struggles on the owner's ineptitude ("The A’s are leaving Oakland — good riddance"). The emotional final game at the Coliseum, a victory for the A's, is a bittersweet moment for fans ("Oakland Athletics fans bid farewell to Coliseum with emotional final win"). The team's owner has apologized to fans for the move, while a congresswoman has outlined her unsuccessful efforts to keep the team in Oakland ("This congresswoman tried to save the Oakland A’s"). The departure is a significant change for the city, ending a long era of baseball in the East Bay ("Farewell From Oakland, Where A’s Fans Lost a 56-Year Fight").

name: Kamindu Mendis
summary: Sri Lankan batsman Kamindu Mendis has made an extraordinary start to his Test cricket career, achieving several notable feats. He has become the fastest Asian batter to score five Test hundreds, equaling the legendary Don Bradman's record. Mendis also set an all-time record by being the second-quickest player to reach 1000 Test runs, behind only Bradman. In a second Test against New Zealand in Galle, Mendis' remarkable performance has drawn comparisons to Bradman's legendary achievements, with experts hailing it as a phenomenal start to his career.

summary: Legendary Britpop band Oasis will embark on a global reunion tour in 2025, with Toronto among the confirmed international cities. The tour will mark the first time the band has performed together since their split in 2009. The reunion has sparked excitement among fans, who eagerly await the announcement of additional tour dates. The band's UK dates have already sold out, leading to speculation that more reunion tour dates will be announced soon. Amid the excitement, there have been reports of tickets being resold at inflated prices, prompting Liam Gallagher to criticize those who are exploiting the demand. Additionally, Oasis is reportedly in talks to produce a documentary ahead of their record-breaking reunion gigs.

summary: Tottenham Hotspur has had a mixed bag of results lately. They had a convincing 3-1 victory over Brentford but lost Dragusin to a red card in a 3-0 win against Qarabag in the Europa League. Despite this, Spurs player Solanke scored his first goal for the team, contributing to the team's comeback. Meanwhile, Spurs investor Paul Viera has increased his stake in the team at a discounted price. In other news, the Spurs are facing turnover in their restaurant partnerships due to lease issues, and Vassell is expected to be out with a foot injury until at least November 1st. As the team looks to the future, they are focusing on developing their bench players and celebrating Tim Duncan's legacy.
